<p>Allentown, Pennsylvania, with its population of 125,845 residents in Lehigh County, presents excellent opportunities for both solar energy and HVAC system upgrades. The city's cold climate creates significant heating demands during winter months, making energy-efficient HVAC systems crucial for homeowners looking to manage utility costs. With PPL serving as the primary electricity provider and rates at 14.2¬¢/kWh, Allentown residents pay above the national average for electricity, making solar panels an increasingly attractive investment for long-term energy savings.</p>

<p>The combination of Pennsylvania's solar incentives, federal tax credits, and Allentown's moderate solar irradiance levels creates favorable conditions for solar adoption. While the cold climate means shorter daylight hours in winter, the cooler temperatures actually improve solar panel efficiency during peak production months. For HVAC systems, the cold Pennsylvania winters require robust heating solutions, while modern heat pumps and high-efficiency furnaces can significantly reduce energy consumption compared to older systems commonly found in Allentown's diverse housing stock.</p>

