  <div><h3 class="font-bold">Best HVAC for Allentown climate?</h3><p>For Allentown's cold climate, high-efficiency gas furnaces (90%+ AFUE) or cold-climate heat pumps are optimal. Ductless mini-splits work well for older homes without ductwork. Air conditioners should have 14-16 SEER ratings minimum. Proper insulation and air sealing are crucial for winter efficiency.</p></div>
  <div><h3 class="font-bold">Does PPL offer solar rebates?</h3><p>PPL doesn't offer direct solar rebates, but they participate in Pennsylvania's net metering program, allowing solar customers to receive credits for excess energy sent to the grid. PPL does offer HVAC rebates for high-efficiency equipment, smart thermostats, and heat pumps through their energy efficiency programs.</p></div>
  <div><h3 class="font-bold">What size solar system do I need in Allentown?</h3><p>Most Allentown homes need 6-8kW systems based on average monthly usage of 900-1,100 kWh. A 6kW system produces approximately 7,200-8,400 kWh annually in Allentown's climate. Factors like roof orientation, shading, and energy usage patterns affect optimal sizing.</p></div>
